From an IT perspective, I will mark this ticket as resolved.

helpdesk-ticket.description: User unable to install Follow You Printing.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: User unable to install Follow You Printing.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Bruce Thompson, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15667
Following are the instructions to install follow you printing on your laptop:
1. Go to start and search for 'Run'. 2. Select 'Run' and type in '\\printers.msoe.edu" 3. You should be able to see a list of printers. 4. Select and double click 'Follow you printing".
There will be 2 options with this name - select the one with spaces between the words.
After this, it should directly install the driver and printing should start working.
Please let us know if this doesn't work so that we can help you further.
Respectfully, Neha Gholap TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT

helpdesk-ticket.subject: PowerFAIDS to Jenzabar Disbursing Financial Aid Issue
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
We are having an issue where when we disburse funds in PowerFAIDS and then run the file in Jenzabar to actually disburse to the student’s account, the Jenzabar process is picking up students that should not be picked up.
In PowerFAIDS, I ran a file to only pick up students who have Federal Loans to disburse and only for Fall and Winter. This happened successfully: [cid:image003.png@01D28C2F.66B05770] One student, one fund, and then 2 disbursements (1 for fall and 1 for winter) with the total there in red.
The next step is to run this in Jenzabar, and this is where the error is happening: [cid:image004.png@01D28C2F.66B05770]
The dollar amounts at the bottom should all be the same, and the total should be the same from PowerFAIDS which is $4948. Jenzabar is pulling in students that start in spring AND even funds that shouldn’t be brought over. The student with the arrows has a fund that I did not even run for in PowerFAIDS and we had zeroed out the fund in PowerFAIDS and put the students on hold.
For background information, we ran our first “simulated aid” file last week where we fake disburse aid to students so that they can see their spring aid on their account. This problem was not occurring before that. Additionally, Julie in Student Accounts blew away the old file today because we thought that was the issue, but these people are still coming even with that gone.
Please help! If someone is calling or coming up before 12:30, please contact Steve (x7224) because I will be back after 12:30. Thank you!
[cid:image002.jpg@01D28C34.D2D0C110]Amanda Wysk | Counselor MSOE Student Financial Services Financial Aid Office 1025 N Broadway |Milwaukee, WI 53202 Office: 414-277-7223 | Direct: 414-277-7511 Office Hours: Monday – Friday 8:00am – 4:30pm

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi all,
We have figured out the problem. When students aren’t registered for spring, their aid cannot be processed and they are pulled into the “Disbursements Under Review” table in Jenzabar. So the errors and then being brought over is Jenzbar’s way of telling us to look at them. I will just have to delete them out each time after I run simulated aid until we can actually disburse for real on March 15th because then they will be registered and things will work fine.
Thank you!
Julie & Steve – I will be running files now and Julie I will tell you what to post and not post when they are all done ☺

helpdesk-note.body:
The source master row for IV transactions has a field for group number control. This was set to 7882 but 7882 was already used as a batch. The field needed to be incremented before a new batch could be entered. This field normally increments automatically.
Jenzabar went ahead and updated the field to 7883. I had Julie try to create the batch again and it was successful. Checked the source master table and the field incremented correctly to the next batch number.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
The source master row for IV transactions has a field for group number control. This was set to 7882 but 7882 was already used as a batch. The field needed to be incremented before a new batch could be entered. This field normally increments automatically. 

Jenzabar went ahead and updated the field to 7883. I had Julie try to create the batch again and it was successful. Checked the source master table and the field incremented correctly to the next batch number.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: blackboard download error
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I’ve run into a problem several times with Blackboard: I get the following error when I try to download a .zip submission from a student. In this case I was trying to grade Jingli Wei’s submission to Lab 9 for my section of SE 1021 (winter, 2016-17). Each time I click the download button on her lab9.zip, I get the same error. I was able to download the solution using the assignment file download from the “full grading center”, but there’s an issue here that should be fixed. It has happened to me with some other student submissions this quarter as well, though the download works just fine for most student submissions.
I am using Google Chrome version 56.0.2924.87 (current release) on my school laptop. But given the error message, it seems pretty clear that the fault is on the server side.
Rob Hasker EECS

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Angela Chandek, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15736
Thank you for the information. Please follow the steps below taken from the Microsoft support website: https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/3045224/can-t-send-an-email-message-when-full-access-permission-is-granted-to-a-shared-mailbox-in-exchange-server
Configure the shared mailbox as an additional account. To do this, follow these steps:
On the File menu, click Info. Click Account Settings, and then click Account Settings. Select your account, and then click Change. In the Change Account dialog box, click More Settings. On the Advanced tab, click Add. Enter the name of the mailbox, and then click OK. After you make this change, the additional mailbox is listed on the Advanced tab in the Microsoft Exchange dialog box.
In the Microsoft Exchange dialog box, click OK. In the Change Account dialog box, click Next. Click Finish, and then click Close.
Respectfully, Gerry TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

    After you make this change, the additional mailbox is listed on the Advanced tab in the Microsoft Exchange dialog box.
  7. In the Microsoft Exchange dialog box, click OK.
  8. In the Change Account dialog box, click Next.
  9. Click Finish, and then click Close.

Are you using one of the Konica printers in RSOB? If so, please select scan on the ribbon at the top of the screen. After that select 'Input Address' at the upper right of the screen, here you will be able to input the address you would like to send your scanned document to. That @ symbol is a little hard to find but it is on the right-hand side of the keyboard that will appear when you select the address box. From there select 'Scan Settings' at the bottom right-hand corner. Finally, just select the start button.
Please let us know if this is helpful.

helpdesk-note.body: She is a member of STEM, who all work at MSOE but aren't technically employed here, so she does not have an msoe.edu email. They use gmail accounts and sync them through Outlook, but hers had gotten desynced last Thurs. Opening up Outlook started a sync process, though the parts that depended on her gmail account did not do anything. I had her log on to her email through the Google site, and it asked for permissions for Outlook to access all of her account stuff. After clicking Allow for that the sync process started and her emails began to show up again.
helpdesk-note.body-html: She is a member of STEM, who all work at MSOE but aren't technically employed here, so she does not have an msoe.edu email. They use gmail accounts and sync them through Outlook, but hers had gotten desynced last Thurs. Opening up Outlook started a sync process, though the parts that depended on her gmail account did not do anything. I had her log on to her email through the Google site, and it asked for permissions for Outlook to access all of her account stuff. After clicking Allow for that the sync process started and her emails began to show up again.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tracy Buczek, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15752
Do you get these delivery failures when you are sending an email to just Ben, or when sending an email to a distribution list? The ucon01 email addresses are access points for the voicemail server to be able to send messages and replies over email. If you get this error when sending a group email through a distribution list, it's possible that this voicemail address got synced into the list and it needs to be updated. If you get it when sending an email to only Ben, it may be that this voicemail address got placed into your cached contacts and it auto-fills this address over Ben's normal address. Respectfully,
Samuel Conroy
TIER 2 SUPPORT TEAM
(414) 277-2834 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu

The ucon01 email addresses are access points for the voicemail server to be able to send messages and replies over email. If you get this error when sending a group email through a distribution list, it's possible that this voicemail address got synced into the list and it needs to be updated. If you get it when sending an email to only Ben, it may be that this voicemail address got placed into your cached contacts and it auto-fills this address over Ben's normal address. 
 
Respectfully,
 
Samuel Conroy

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tracy Buczek, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15752
Thank you so much. Since we have not heard from you in 17 hours, I will assume that this worked, and that you did not receive a rejection email. This tells me there may be a problem with the outlook desktop application on your computer. I ask that you first try restarting your computer if it has been on for a while. Next, I ask that you try to repair Office. A step-by-step guide for this can be found here: http://msoe.freshservice.com/support/solutions/articles/1000028837 If this does not work, you may try installing Office 2016 from the Software Center as it is a more up-to-date version of the program and will most likely not cause the same issues. To get to the software center, open the start menu and just type, "Software Center." The link to get to the software center will be at the top of the menu after that. After clicking the link, Software Center will open and you will be able to search for Microsoft Office Professional 2016 and install this. Outlook 2016 is included in this package as well as all other Microsoft Office programs such as Word 2016, Excel 2016, etc. The download and installation process could take up to an hour or more, so plan accordingly if you choose to do this.
A solution for clearing the nickname cache can be found here: https://moodle2.grok.lsu.edu/article.aspx?articleid=18029 This involves clicking the little, 'x' next to a persons name. Hopefully this works if autocomplete is the only issue you are facing.
Respectfully, Gerry TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

Hi Nathan Hansen, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15759
Hello,
From you Outlook client: file - manage rules and alerts - new rule - apply rule on message I receive - next - where my name is in the To or CC box - next - redirect it to people or public group - click the link that says people or public group and enter your email address - next - next - give it a name if you want, set up rule options and then click finish.
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Gary Shimek, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15766
In order to change the password for a local account on Windows 7, there are two methods. You can log on to the account you want to change the password on, hit Control-Alt-Delete, and click on Change a password.... The other way is to log on to any account with administrator access, go to the Control Panel, click on User Accounts, click on User Accounts, and click on Manage User Accounts. From here you should see a list of all the accounts that are on the computer, and you can select the one that you want and click on Reset Password.... Either way, it should then ask you for the old password and then allow you to enter a new password.
Respectfully,
Samuel Conroy
TIER 2 SUPPORT TEAM
(414) 277-2834 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu

From here you should see a list of all the accounts that are on the computer, and you can select the one that you want and click on Reset Password.... Thanks, Thomas Schleich Assistant Systems Administrator helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

Jeremiah

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jeremiah Buddenhagen, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15796
If you took a quarter off and did not return your laptop to us, then you will be charged a fee because keeping the laptop for the quarter you took off would be considered stealing as the laptop is property of MSOE until it is gifted to you upon Graduation. If this is the case and you cannot register due to a lost/stolen laptop fee, then I suggest you pay said fee in order to be able to register for classes again. If you have paid this fee already, and it still shows up on your account, please let us know. You are also welcome to respond with any more questions you may have about the laptop fee. Thank you.
Respectfully, Gerry TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-ticket.subject: S-344 Matlab Errors
helpdesk-ticket.description: Bench #7 in S-344 had a bunch of matlab errors. I uninstalled matlab through the control panel and matlab started to install automatically through the software center. The installation came up with an error and now says matlab is installed which it is not. I checked through the control panel and matlab is not in the list of programs to uninstall. Do not know why the software center thinks it is installed as I do not have a shortcut and if you search for matlab only item found is a empty matlab folder in documents.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Bench #7 in S-344 had a bunch of matlab errors.  I uninstalled matlab through the control panel and matlab started to install automatically through the software center.  The installation came up with an error and now says matlab is installed which it is not. I checked through the control panel and matlab is not in the list of programs to uninstall.  Do not know why the software center thinks it is installed as I do not have a shortcut and if you search for matlab only item found is a empty matlab folder in documents.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jim Frommell, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15802
I'm sorry that reinstalling MatLab is such an odd process, I have gone ahead and reinstalled it for you.
You were right to search for the MatLab files, but for some reason MatLab does not like showing folders when searched for. Instead, you can find them inside the C drive in the 'Program Files'. After deleting these files Software Center will still think that MatLab is installed, so you can go into 'Configuration Manager' and the 'Actions' tab. There you can run 'Application Deployment Evaluation Cycle', 'Machine Policy Retrieval & Evaluation Cycle', as well as 'Software Updates Deployment Evaluation Cycle'. If Software Center still thinks MatLab is installed you can also open the Command Prompt as an admin and run 'gpupdate /force'. At this point MatLab will automatically start installing, if not you can click install yourself.
I hope that this is helpful to you, and if you have any further questions please feel free to contact us.
Respectfully, Karolina Klimont TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Patrick Dwyer, Here are the instructions for setting up the password self help portal: To register your account with the portal: 1. Go to pwdreg.msoe.edu. 2. Enter your current MSOE email and password. 3. Click "Next." 4. Enter your current MSOE password and click "Next." 5. Answer at least 3 of the questions provided. The answers are not case sensitive.
You will only have to register your account once.
Once you have registered your account:
To reset your password: 1. Go to pwd.msoe.edu. 2. Enter your MSOE username. 3. Answer at least 2 of the 3 questions provided with the same answers you gave when registering your account. The answers are not case sensitive. 4. Select "Password Reset." 5. Create a password, different from your previous 4 passwords, that is at least 8 characters long containing the following: an uppercase letter, a lowercase letter, a number, and a symbol (ie. ! @ $). 6. Re-enter the new password and click "Next."
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Patrick Dwyer,
Here are the instructions for setting up the password self help portal:
To register your account with the portal:
1. Go to pwdreg.msoe.edu.
2. Enter your current MSOE email and password.
3. Click "Next."
4. Enter your current MSOE password and click "Next."
5. Answer at least 3 of the questions provided. The answers are not case sensitive.
 
You will only have to register your account once.
 
Once you have registered your account:
 
To reset your password:
1. Go to pwd.msoe.edu.
2. Enter your MSOE username.
3. Answer at least 2 of the 3 questions provided with the same answers you gave when registering your account. The answers are not case sensitive.
4. Select "Password Reset."
5. Create a password, different from your previous 4 passwords, that is at least 8 characters long containing the following: an uppercase letter, a lowercase letter, a number, and a symbol (ie. ! @ $).
6. Re-enter the new password and click "Next."


Peter Pfister
Help Desk Coordinator
414.277.7202

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Ashley Fernandez, Here are some instructions as well as some basic information about your password. Passwords expire 90 days after setting. Your last 3 passwords are remembered and cannot be reused until they drop off. Have a plan for when your password is about to expire. The Help Desk cannot reset your password unless you visit the desk with your ID. We must positively identify you before we reset. When the Help Desk resets your password it will be to the default MSOE password.
Msoe + 6 digit ID number + 6 digit birthday (mmddyy). Example: Msoe123456010203 Jan 2, 2003.
2 weeks prior to expiration a single email reminder is sent. 1 week out starts daily email reminders. I strongly suggest not letting it expire and to register your account with our password self-help portal.
To register your account with the portal: 1. Go to pwdreg.msoe.edu. 2. Enter your current MSOE email and password. 3. Click "Next." 4. Enter your current MSOE password and click "Next." 5. Answer at least 3 of the questions provided. The answers are not case sensitive.
You will only have to register your account once.
Once you have registered your account:
To reset your password: 1. Go to pwd.msoe.edu. 2. Enter your MSOE username. 3. Answer at least 2 of the 3 questions provided with the same answers you gave when registering your account. The answers are not case sensitive. 4. Select "Password Reset." 5. Create a password, different from your previous 4 passwords, that is at least 8 characters long containing the following: an uppercase letter, a lowercase letter, a number, and a symbol (ie. ! @ $). 6. Re-enter the new password and click "Next."
To unlock your account: 1. Go to pwd.msoe.edu. 2. Enter your MSOE username. 3. Answer at least 2 of the 3 questions provided with the same answers you gave when registering your account. The answers are not case sensitive. 4. Select "Account Unlock" and click "Next".
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jordan Bauer, Thank you for contacting IT Help Desk. To install software center follow these steps:
1. Make sure the computer is wired in or connected to "Internal Domain" 2. Go to Computer > M Drive > Software Center Install > install.bat 3. It will install the software center 4. Search "cmd" in the start option, right click on "Command Prompt" and run as administrator and hit "Yes". 5. Type "gpupdate/force" and run the group policy. 6. Restart the computer 7. Go to "Configuration Manager" in "Control Panel" 8. Go to "Actions" tab and run "Machine Policy Retrieval & Evaluation Cycle" 9. Software Center will work just fine in 30 minutes Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15859

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Jordan Bauer,
      Thank you for contacting IT Help Desk. To install software center follow these steps:

1. Make sure the computer is wired in or connected to "Internal Domain" 
2. Go to Computer > M Drive > Software Center Install > install.bat 
3. It will install the software center 
4. Search "cmd" in the start option, right click on "Command Prompt" and run as administrator and hit "Yes". 
5. Type "gpupdate/force" and run the group policy. 
6. Restart the computer 
7. Go to "Configuration Manager" in "Control Panel" 
8. Go to "Actions" tab and run "Machine Policy Retrieval & Evaluation Cycle" 
9. Software Center will work just fine in 30 minutes

helpdesk-note.body:
Setting up the process in play. Asked Tom to create a test student refund under my name in the meantime.
Using JICS test database now. Had to have Managed Services download the Client Application Service on the test JICS server so that we can test the epayment receipt emails.
Running into issues with creating the test student refunds. The bank information for students and vendors has a begin date for each person and that needs to be a date earlier than the echeck dates in order to be able to issue them as epayments. They can't even be the same day... must be earlier.
There is a generic vendor ID that is used to run student refunds as epayments. This generic id needs to have dummy account information for the process the student refunds:
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Setting up the process in play. Asked Tom to create a test student refund under my name in the meantime. 

Using JICS test database now. Had to have Managed Services download the Client Application Service on the test JICS server so that we can test the epayment receipt emails. 

Running into issues with creating the test student refunds. The bank information for students and vendors has a begin date for each person and that needs to be a date earlier than the echeck dates in order to be able to issue them as epayments. They can't even be the same day... must be earlier. 

There is a generic vendor ID that is used to run student refunds as epayments. This generic id needs to have dummy account information for the process the student refunds:

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Tower No Internet
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
as of Saturday the router in my roommate and my's room has stopped giving out any internet connection. The wireless network is still there however when we go to connect to it it gives us the "No internet" message. To work around this, we connected our devices to the Tower wireless internet. This has been giving us bad connections so far and both him and I have been experience incredibly long load times as well as high latency. A couple of times the internet itself has dropped and given us the "No Internet" message. We're wondering what we can do to either bring back our router or how to increase the strength of the Tower's wireless internet.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Alexander Weislak, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/15900
I apologize for the inconvenience. The Towers' internet network is in a transition phase, so there are issues with the connection in some rooms. Because of this, the tower wifi is under a heavier load than usual because more people have to use it. I will route this ticket to the network team so they can help to resolve the issue, but first I need to gather some information.
1. What is your room number? 2. Is it a problem with your router or the ethernet cable coming into your room? You can test this by plugging a laptop directly into the wall with the cable that plugs into your router.
